column155: The 18 self-directed activities that occurred within this fiscal year included 3 social media reading challenges, 8 grab-and-go kits for the Out-of-School Time Grant, 5 First 5 bilingual craft kits, 1 Winter Open House bag (included books), and 1 Summer Reading Program bag (included books and crafts). The spring, summer, and winter social media reading challenges were conducted via Beanstack. The Out-of-School Time Grant grab-and-go literacy kits were provided to participants in 2 apartment complexes during a span of 8 weeks. The bilingual craft kits were provided to preschools and elementary schools for children to take home. The Winter Open House grab-and-go bag and the Summer Reading Program bag were provided to participants to read and enjoy at home.

In addition, they created "take and Make: kits that included materials and instructions for completing self-directed activities at home.
